  <CaptionedBlock heading="Your Labradoodle's First Week at Home" imageAlt="Labradoodle puppy settling into a set-up playpen during its first week home" imagePosition="left">
    <p>Day 0: we deliver, free, at a time that suits you. The playpen, bed, water, and toys are set up before your Labradoodle explores the room, and we walk you through all 30+ starter-kit items in person, including the coat-care routine. Learn more about <a href="/delivery" class="underline underline-offset-2 text-[var(--color-accent-hover)]">how our free home delivery and setup works</a>.</p>
    <p>Days 1 to 3: keep it calm. A fixed feeding routine with measured portions, the toilet pads where we placed them, and gentle play that helps your puppy settle into its new room.</p>
    <p>Days 4 to 7: the routine sticks, and now is the time to build good habits. Book your free first lesson with an AVS-certified trainer to channel that Labrador energy early, and start short, positive brushing sessions so your Labradoodle grows up loving its grooming. See <a href="/free-training" class="underline underline-offset-2 text-[var(--color-accent-hover)]">what the free AVS-certified training lesson covers</a>.</p>
  </CaptionedBlock>

